  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Lightclient should use req/resp protocol of eth2 to communicate and receive updates. Since lightclient should be separate package/binary it needs access to code for making req/resp. \r\n\r\nExact gossip and rpc methods are not yet specified but we could invent our own for POC purposes.\r\n\r\nI would keep like existing rpc method implementation like blocks_by_range and others in lodestar since lightclient doesn't have need for those and it could complicate package extraction.\r\n\r\nNew @chainsafe/lodestar-networking should probably contain, libp2p related code, req/resp implementation, abstract gossip implementation, peer managment.\r\n\r\ncc @ChainSafe/eth2-0 ",
